(1635, 144, 'left_content_2', 'So, why should you consider roof coatings for your property anyway? To put it simply, they improve the performance of your roof and will increase its lifespan, too. They can either be sprayed or rolled onto the roof’s surface to protect the building from leaks and water damage.\r\n\r\nAs a single protective membrane, roof coatings don’t have seams, fasteners, or flashing capabilities. Here are some of the top benefits of flat roof coatings:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Water Protection</strong>: Since roof coatings consist of a single, seamless membrane, any form of water will be almost completely blocked from ruining your roof system and causing leaks. Even on the off-chance that a leak develops, it will be much easier to fix.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Energy Efficiency</strong>: Our commercial roofing coatings are reflective, meaning they bounce UV rays off your building instead of absorbing them. This will keep your space cooler overall, meaning you’ll have lower energy bills and happier employees!</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Easy Installations</strong>: A roof coating is very easy to install, whether you choose to have it sprayed on or rolled on. This means installing roof coatings will typically be less expensive than other roofing types.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
